info.senderName: NWS Duluth (Northeast Minnesota and Northern Wisconsin)
info.headline: Winter Storm Warning issued March 10 at 9:37PM CST until March 13 at 12:00AM CST by NWS Duluth
info.description: ...WINTER STORM WARNING NOW IN EFFECT FROM NOON CST SATURDAY TO 1 AM CDT MONDAY... * WHAT...Heavy snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 5 to 8 inches, except 8 to 14 inches for the higher terrain of the North Shore. Winds gusting to 40 mph near the Lake Superior shore. * WHERE...North St. Louis, Central St. Louis, Northern Aitkin, South Aitkin, Carlton and South St. Louis and Pine Counties. This includes the Tribal Lands of the Fond du Lac Band, the Mille Lacs Band, East Lake, Lena Lake, Hinckley and, Big Sandy Lake areas and the Bois Forte Band, Nett Lake and, Lake Vermilion areas. * WHEN...From noon CST Saturday to 1 AM CDT Monday. * IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult.
info.instruction: If you must travel, keep an extra flashlight, food, and water in your vehicle in case of an emergency. The latest road conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1. Road conditions can also be found at 511mn.org for Minnesota or 511wi.gov for Wisconsin.
